## How to use design docs

A design doc records the context, decision, and trade-offs for a significant architectural choice. Write one when:
- The decision is hard to reverse.
- Multiple reasonable approaches exist and you need to justify which you chose.
- You want future contributors (human or agent) to understand the "why".

